Moves all the elements of `other` into `self`, leaving `other` empty.

# Panics

Panics if the new capacity exceeds `isize::MAX` _bytes_.

# Examples

```
let mut vec = vec![1, 2, 3];
let mut vec2 = vec![4, 5, 6];
vec.append(&mut vec2);
assert_eq!(vec, [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]);
assert_eq!(vec2, []);
```
